Package: rsalad
Title: A mix of useful R functions that are good for you
Version: 0.0.2.2
Authors@R: "Dean Attali <daattali@gmail.com> [aut, cre]"
Description: Collection of functions that help with easily manipulating
    data.frames (e.g. converting variables to factors, rearranging variables)
    and improve usability and functionality of knitr::spin (e.g. better
    handling of working directories and output directories).
URL: https://github.com/daattali/rsalad
Depends:
    R (>= 3.0.2)
Imports:
    dplyr (>= 0.3.0),
    magrittr (>= 1.5)
Suggests:
    knitr (>= 1.7),
    lazyeval (>= 0.1.9),
    markdown (>= 0.7),
    microbenchmark (>= 1.4),
    nycflights13 (>= 0.1),
    R.utils (>= 1.34.0),
    testthat (>= 0.9.1)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
VignetteBuilder: knitr
